    "text": "Sleep is only one input, and the others didn't cooperate. Your 8.4 hours last night was genuinely excellent, well above your 7.4-hour weekly average, but recovery scores lean heavily on overnight heart signals, and yours are lagging: HRV came in at 61 ms against a 30-day average of 64.4 ms, your 7-day HRV trend reads suppressed, and resting heart rate is 58 bpm versus a 55.9 baseline. Yesterday's 75-minute run with a 15.4 load is likely still being processed; autonomic recovery often trails a hard session by a day even when sleep is long. So 56% isn't your tracker ignoring the sleep, it's the sleep partially offsetting fatigue. Expect the score to rebound within a day or two if you keep today moderate, and note your ring doesn't track strain, so the run's load is the best effort marker we have.",
